data.meta_desc: I put 12 socks in the washer and only 11 came out. This happens a lot. Where does the missing sock go? Lee Ballentine surrealist poet & engineer five time T This problem has recently been solved by physicists at MIT. The equations have been known for some time but the interpretation was only worked out last year. Through a process related to quantum dynamics, if a pair of socks are entangled with just the right color and geometry one of them can no longer remain in this part of the cosmos and it tunnels through to the Sock Nebula.
